            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Price</td>
              <td class="comparison-highlight">Free</td>
              <td>Paid on iOS</td>
              <td>Free (with ads) or paid</td>
              <td>Free (with ads) or paid</td>
            </tr>
            <tr>
              <td>Account required</td>
              <td class="comparison-highlight">No</td>
              <td>Optional</td>
              <td>Yes</td>
              <td>Yes</td>
            </tr>
          </tbody>
        </table>
      </div>
      <div class="inline-cta">
        <%= cta_button %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Already using Anki? -->
  <section class="longform-section">
    <div class="longform-container longform-container--narrow">
      <h2 class="longform-heading">Already invested in Anki? You don't have to start over.</h2>
      <p class="longform-body">If you've spent months or years building Anki decks, that work isn't wasted. Language Den imports .apkg files directly. Your cards come with you into a modern app that's actually designed for language learning.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">You can also import from CSV files or add words manually. However your vocabulary lives right now, Language Den can work with it.</p>

      <div class="screenshot-single">
        <div class="screenshot-filled">
          <img src="/images/anki-import.png" alt="Language Den import screen for importing Anki .apkg deck files">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight-box">
        <p><strong>You keep everything you've built.</strong> You just get a better tool to learn with.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- How fast -->
  <section class="longform-section longform-section--alt">
    <div class="longform-container longform-container--narrow">
      <h2 class="longform-heading">Get started in under 60 seconds</h2>
      <p class="longform-body" style="margin-bottom: 40px;">No sign-up forms. No onboarding wizards. No email verification. Here's the entire process:</p>
      <div class="steps">
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">1</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Download the app</h3>
            <p>It's free. Open it. That's it. There's no account to create.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">2</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Add your first words</h3>
            <p>Type a word, import an existing deck, or capture something with Quick Notes. However you want to start, start.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">3</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Build your flashcards</h3>
            <p>Add definitions, example sentences, conjugations, and images. Create them yourself, or optionally let AI do it for you.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="step">
          <div class="step-number">4</div>
          <div class="step-content">
            <h3>Review and remember</h3>
            <p>Spaced repetition does the rest. You just show up, review your cards, and watch your vocabulary grow.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="inline-cta">
        <%= cta_button %>
        <p class="inline-cta-note">You'll be reviewing your first cards in under a minute.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Imagine -->
  <section class="longform-section">
    <div class="longform-container longform-container--narrow">
      <h2 class="longform-heading">Imagine this</h2>
      <p class="longform-body">It's three months from now. You open Language Den for your morning review. It takes ten minutes. The app shows you exactly the words you need to see today. Not the ones you already know. Not random ones. The ones you're about to forget.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">You get through the stack. Some words are easy now. They used to be hard. Some are still tricky. The app knows that and will show them to you again soon.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">You close the app. Ten minutes. And in those ten minutes, you've reinforced hundreds of words. Words that are actually sticking this time. Words you'll remember next week, next month, next year.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">That's not a fantasy. That's how spaced repetition works. And Language Den makes it effortless.</p>

      <div class="screenshot-single">
        <div class="screenshot-filled">
          <img src="/images/home.png" alt="Language Den home screen showing vocabulary decks">
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="highlight-box highlight-box--green">
        <p><strong>The best time to start building your vocabulary was a year ago. The second best time is right now.</strong></p>
      </div>

      <div class="inline-cta">
        <%= cta_button %>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Objections / FAQ -->
  <section class="longform-section longform-section--alt">
    <div class="longform-container longform-container--narrow">
      <h2 class="longform-heading">You might be wondering...</h2>
      <div class="faq-list">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"Is it really free? What's the catch?"</h3>
          <p>There is no catch. Language Den is free to download and free to use. No subscription. No paywall. No "premium" features locked behind a monthly fee. The free version will always be free.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"What's FSRS? Is it better than what Anki uses?"</h3>
          <p>FSRS (Free Spaced Repetition Scheduler) is a modern, open-source scheduling algorithm. It's more accurate than SM-2, which Anki used as its default for over 15 years. FSRS adapts to your personal memory patterns and schedules reviews more efficiently. You don't need to know any of this to use the app. It just works.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"Does it have AI features?"</h3>
          <p>Yes, as an optional extra. You can connect an OpenRouter API key to auto-generate flashcard content like definitions, example sentences, and conjugations. But the app is fully functional without it. AI is there if you want it. It's not required.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"What if my language isn't supported?"</h3>
          <p>It is. Language Den works with any language you can type. There's no fixed language list. If your keyboard can produce the characters, Language Den can teach you the words.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"I have years of Anki decks. Can I bring them over?"</h3>
          <p>Yes. Language Den imports .apkg files directly. You can also import from CSV. Your existing work comes with you.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"Do I need to create an account?"</h3>
          <p>No. Language Den uses your existing iCloud (Apple ID) for syncing. There's nothing to sign up for. Open the app and start learning.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>"What if I don't like it?"</h3>
          <p>Delete it. It's free. You haven't lost anything. But give it a week of daily reviews first. That's when spaced repetition starts to click, and you'll feel the difference.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final push -->
  <section class="longform-section">
    <div class="longform-container longform-container--narrow">
      <h2 class="longform-heading">You have two choices right now</h2>
      <p class="longform-body"><strong>Option one:</strong> Close this page. Go back to whatever app you've been using. Keep fighting with clunky interfaces, missing features, and tools that weren't built for language learning. Keep forgetting words you've studied three times already.</p>
      <p class="longform-body"><strong>Option two:</strong> Download Language Den. It takes 30 seconds. Add your first words. Start a review. Feel what it's like to use a vocabulary app that was actually built for what you're trying to do.</p>
      <p class="longform-body">It's free. There's no risk. There's no account to create. There's nothing to lose except the words you keep forgetting.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Final CTA -->
  <section class="cta">
    <div class="cta-container">
      <h2>Stop forgetting. Start learning.</h2>
      <p>Free. No account. No ads. No tracking. Built for language learners.</p>
      <%= cta_button %>
      <p class="cta-sub">Available on iOS. Download takes seconds.</p>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>
